## The Eight Invariants — Never Violate These
INV-1: ConnectionManager is the ONLY owner of connection state.
INV-2: EventRegistry is the ONLY source of truth for registered events.
INV-3: Startup validation runs before the server accepts any connection.
INV-4: Handler exceptions NEVER kill the connection. Always caught, formatted as __error__, emitted.
INV-5: emits/broadcasts on @socket.on() are documentation metadata ONLY. Never control behavior.
INV-6: Security layers run in fixed order: Origin → Auth → Size → Pydantic → RateLimit → Middleware → DI → Handler.
INV-7: ALL state mutations are protected by asyncio.Lock. No exceptions.
INV-8: No circular imports. Dependency flows one direction only.

## Build Order — Follow This Exactly
Build modules in this exact order. Each depends on the previous.
1.  pyproject.toml + _version.py
2.  errors.py
3.  types.py
4.  connection.py
5.  backends/base.py + backends/memory.py
6.  registry.py
7.  session.py
8.  security/origins.py + security/ratelimit.py + security/auth.py
9.  middleware.py
10. di.py
11. router.py
12. manager.py
13. rooms.py
14. app.py
15. adapters/fastapi.py
16. docs/engine.py + docs/router.py + docs/ui/
17. __init__.py
18. tests/ (unit first, then integration)

