## Code Rules — Non-Negotiable
- Never bare except: — always except SpecificException:
- Never print() in library code — always logger.*()
- Never asyncio.run() inside async context
- Always re-raise asyncio.CancelledError — never swallow it
- Always async with for locks — never manual acquire/release
- Never relative imports — always absolute from socketspec.*
- Never magic numbers — always named constants
- Never Any in public API surface
- Use X | None not Optional[X]
- Use dict/list/tuple not Dict/List/Tuple

## Test Rules
- Test names: test_<what>_<condition>_<expected_outcome>
- One primary assertion per test
- No shared mutable state between tests
- Mock at boundaries (BackendAdapter), not internals
- asyncio_mode = "auto" is set — no @pytest.mark.asyncio needed

## Commit Message Format
type(scope): description
Types: feat, fix, docs, test, refactor, chore, security, adapter, backend
Example: feat(registry): add deprecated flag to EventDefinition

## Wire Protocol — All Messages Use This Envelope
Client → Server: {"event": "event_name", "payload": {...}}
Server → Client: {"event": "event_name", "payload": {...}}
Error:           {"event": "__error__", "payload": {"code": "...", "event": "...", "message": "...", "request_id": "...", "details": {...}}}

## Reserved Event Names — Never Register These
__connect__, __disconnect__, __error__, __ping__, __pong__,
__auth_expiring__, __session_expiring__, __idle_warning__,
__server_shutdown__, __refresh_auth__

## When You Finish a Module
- Run: mypy src/socketspec --strict
- Run: ruff check src/
- Run: pytest tests/ -v
- All must pass before moving to the next module in the build order.

## When You Change System Structure
Update .context/SYSTEM_CURRENT.md to reflect the change.
If the change adds a module, update Section 3 (Module Map).
If it changes a flow, update Section 4 (Data Flows).
If it makes a new technical decision, add it to Section 6 (Active Decisions).

